The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Doda, Feb. 25 (PTI): Forty-one passengers were killed when a Jammu-bound bus rolled down into the Neeru river in Doda district today. At least 13 persons were injured.           
	The bus skidded off the road and fell into Neeru at 8.15am. Thirty-nine people died on the spot and two in hospital. Nine persons were airlifted to the Jammu government hospital.                   
	 New Delhi: Former Union minister Sukh Ram was handed a three-year jail term on Wednesday in a 1996 assets case. However, the sentence on Sukh Ram, from whose houses the CBI had seized Rs 3.61 crore, will remain suspended till April 23, by when he has been asked to pay a Rs 2-lakh fine. The 82-year-old was given bail later.                   
	 New Delhi: The government has asked the National Commission for Scheduled Castes to suggest amendments to a controversial proposed law exempting top academic institutions from most job quotas. The bill was handed over to the panel after Sonia Gandhi expressed displeasure over its current form.                  
	 New Delhi: Parliament has ratified an ordinance to launch new central universities signed by the President in January amid opposition from BJP members who accused the government of impropriety in promulgating an ordinance just before polls. The Rajya Sabha on Tuesday night approved the bill, clearing the way for the government to launch the new universities.                  
	 New Delhi: The Supreme Court has asked the Tamil Nadu government to explain by Thursday who had authorised armed police to enter Madras High Court and assured the striking lawyers that action would be taken on the alleged police excesses on them.                   
	 Dehri-on-Sone (PTI): A top Maoist commander, wanted in several cases including the 2005 Jehanabad jail break, has been arrested from Dalmianagar. Satyendra Kushwaha was going to catch a bus for Rohtas.                                                                                                                           
